{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, an LLM is a very prominent storyteller but unfortunately lacks the property of Agency.",
    "Such a machine lacks the ability to construct a world model, does not have moral understanding and always needs a prompt to start operating, therefore it is the human that undertakes the role of the agent.",
    "NI on the other hand is a biological construct that creates a world model, can make predictions and planning, can interact with the environment, presents emergent phenomena such as consciousness, and supersedes the current abilities of AI under unprecedented circumstances thus presents the property of Agency.",
    "We explored both NI and AI potentials and limitations, enumerating in the process some significant sociological and ethical consequences that are derived from AI progress, up to the point when AI finally matches human intellect, if it ever does.",
    "We showed that NI and AI represent two distinct forms of intelligence with each of them having unique underlying instrumentations and capabilities, but also unique limitations."
  ]
}